<div class='communityQuestionAndAnswer'>
<div class='communityQuestion'>
<div class='questionText'>
<a href="/questions/1086540-i-am-wondering-how-people-liked-the-way-it">I am wondering how people liked the way it ended. I don&#39;t want to say much about this because it could be a spoiler, but I felt sad. Maybe just because I was saying goodbye to an old friend by this time--the friend being the book itself. What do you think?</a>
</div>
<div class='communityQAFooter questionFooter'>
<ul class='questionFooterActions'>
<li class='footerItem like'>
<span class='likeItContainer' id='like_container_community_question_1086540'><a id="like_count_community_question_1086540" rel="nofollow" href="/rating/voters/1086540?resource_type=CommunityQuestion"><span class="likesCount">3 likes</span></a>&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;<a rel="nofollow" class="jsLike like_it" href="https://www.goodreads.com/user/new?remember=true&amp;return_url=%2Fbook%2Fshow%2F50365.A_Suitable_Boy">like</a></span>

</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionTimestamp'>
<a href="/questions/1086540-i-am-wondering-how-people-liked-the-way-it">4 years ago</a>
</li>
<li class='footerItem communityQuestionPermalink'>
<a href="/questions/1086540-i-am-wondering-how-people-liked-the-way-it">See all 7 answers</a>
</li>
</ul>
</div>

</div>
<div class='allCommunityAnswers'>
<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/8400193-karry"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1334839048i/8400193._UX100_CR0,16,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/8400193-karry">Karry</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">I was both sad and disappointed. I thought that the way the author handled the Maan and Firoz issues was very good and was hoping that Lata&apos;s situatio<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">I was both sad and disappointed. I thought that the way the author handled the Maan and Firoz issues was very good and was hoping that Lata's situation would be concluded similarly, not with kid gloves but gently. When my husband and I finished it last night we were very disappointed and although we are less so today we still feel like it was disjointed and so sad. I'll miss Lata's mother and many of the strong characters who became part of our family for the weeks we read it. <a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
</div>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerFooter'>

